The paper deals with sentiment analysis of news videos using audio, textual, and visual features. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) categories. Additionally, the paper uses facial expression recognition and speech analysis, which are related to Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) categories. Finally, the paper applies state-of-the-art computational methods, which are related to Machine Learning (cs.LG) category.
